Position is fully remote! Ideally, looking for a candidate local/close to Baltimore.

Full time opportunity!

Competitive salary and amazing benefits!

Must have 3+ years of experience in React!

SUMMARY: Our client is seeking an experienced and highly motivated Software Applications Developer to join the team. The successful candidate will be responsible for designing, developing, implementing, updating, and maintaining the customized information processing systems for ABET Headquarters operations. The Software Applications Developer will help create a new enterprise-level web application. This position reports directly to the Software Architect.

ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES include the following. Other duties may be assigned.

• Responsible for helping to develop the next iteration of the Accreditation Management System, a large web application that makes it possible for the people working with ABET to do their jobs.

• Work with a tight-knit and agile team to design, develop, and test an enterprise-level web application.

• Work with Restful services and reporting tools.

QUALIFICATION REQUIREMENTS: To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform each essential duty satisfactorily. The required skills listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill, and/or ability required.

EDUCATION and/or EXPERIENCE:

• Bachelor’s degree in computer science or a related field from an accredited institution

• 3+ years of experience programming in JavaScript, React, HTML, CSS, UI and UX development

REQUIRED KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS AND ABILITIES:

• Desired experience:

o Experience with React, JavaScript (experience in other related JavaScript frameworks will be reviewed - Angular or any other databinding JS)

o ReactJS, HTML5, SASS, SCSS, Bootstrap

o Agile/Scrum

o Azure or AWS experience is a big plus

o Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills.

o Ability to work as both part of a team and independently.

o Good communication and interpersonal skills to work collaboratively with team members.

• Helpful knowledge of:

o C#, .NET Framework 3.5+, ASP.Net/MVC, and MS Visual Studio
• o MS SQL

For immediate consideration, please send your updated resume to dpatterson@eliassen.com
